Material Library – Quick Reference
Class Hierarchy
    -Material

        Base class that contains the common properties of any material (id, name, density, etc.).

    -FormulatedProduct

        Concrete subclass of Material. Represents a finished product that is made from other materials.
        Adds its own properties such as massAmount, massUnit, volAmount, and volUnit.

    -Reagent

        Concrete subclass of Material. Represents a raw material that can be used as an ingredient.

    -Ingredient Type
        type Ingredient = FormulatedProduct | Reagent;
        The Ingredient type is a union that allows a variable to hold either a FormulatedProduct or a Reagent. Used to type components of Formulated Products